url = 'https://www.google.com/finance/markets/most-active?hl=en'

# set maximum number of retries to 3
max_retries = 3

# set delay time between retries to 10 seconds
retry_delay = 10

# configure logging to write errors to a file
logging.basicConfig(filename='errors.log', level=logging.ERROR)

# try request multiple times in case of failure
for i in range(max_retries):
    try:
        response = requests.get(url, timeout=10)
        response.raise_for_status()
    except requests.exceptions.RequestException as e:
        logging.error(f'Retrying request {i+1}/{max_retries} after error: {e}')
        time.sleep(retry_delay)
    else:
        soup = bs(response.text, 'html.parser')
        tables = soup.find(class_="Vd323d")
        break

# if loop finished without a successful response, raise an exception
else:
    logging.error(f'Error: Maximum number of retries ({max_retries}) exceeded')
    raise requests.exceptions.RequestException(f'Maximum number of retries exceeded for url: {url}')

# define empty lists to store data for each variable
Symbols =[]
Names = []
Prices = []
Changes = []
Per_Changes = []

# iterate through each row of the table and extract relevant data for each variable
table_index = tables.find_all(class_ = 'COaKTb')
for row in table_index[0:]:
    index = row.text
    Symbols.append(index)

table_name = tables.find_all(class_ = 'ZvmM7')
for row2 in table_name[0:]:
    full_name = row2.text
    Names.append(full_name)

table_price = tables.find_all(class_ = 'YMlKec')
for row3 in table_price[0:]:
    stock_price = row3.text
    Prices.append(stock_price)

table_change = tables.select('.P2Luy.Ebnabc, .P2Luy.Ez2Ioe')
for row4 in table_change[0:]:
    price_change = row4.text
    Changes.append(price_change)

    
table_per_change = tables.find_all(class_ = 'JwB6zf')
for row5 in table_per_change[0:]:
    stock_per_change = row5.text
    Per_Changes.append(stock_per_change)

# Clean the columns
df['price($)'] = df['price($)'].str.strip('$').astype(float)

df['change'] = df['change'].str.replace(r'\$', '', regex=True).astype(float)

df['%_change'] = df['%_change'].str.strip('%').astype(float)
